/ ThreeJS Project Architecture Guide

// Core Principles
- Keep it simple (KISS): Start with basic structure, add complexity only when needed
- Follow SOLID principles for maintainable code
- Focus on readability and clear organization

// Project Structure
/src
  /core          // Core setup (renderer, camera, scene)
  /scenes        // Different scenes/experiences
  /components    // Reusable 3D elements
  /utils         // Helper functions
  /materials     // Custom materials/shaders
  /controls      // User interactions

// Key Best Practices
1. Organization
- One class = one responsibility
- Keep files small and focused
- Use clear, descriptive names
- Comment complex logic

2. Performance
- Clean up unused resources
- Use simple geometries when possible
- Be careful with lights and shadows
- Implement proper dispose methods

3. Development
- Implement debug mode
- Handle window resizing
- Add error handling

4. Code Quality
- Write reusable components
- Implement proper cleanup

Remember:
- Start simple, add features gradually
- Document your code